Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setPtnPinUSE(25.10)                                        setPtnPinUSE(25.10)

Name
       setPtnPinUSE - Allows you to change the USE property of a partition pin

Syntax
       setPtnPinUSE

       [-help]

       <ptnName>

       <pinName>

       <pinUse>

       Allows you to change the USE property of a partition pin.

       Note: A partition pin can also be an I/O pin if the partition is a top-
       level cell.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each setPtnPinUSE parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setPtnPinUse

       <ptnName>
              Specifies the name of the partition, blackbox or top-level  cell
              name.

              Data_type: string, required

       <pinName>
              Specifies the pin name.

              Data_type: string, required

       <pinUse>
              The  choices  represent USE properties, SIGNAL | CLOCK | ANALOG,
              that you can change with this command.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              * The following command sets the USE property of pin A in parti-
                tion PTN1 to CLOCK:

                setPtnPinUSE PTN1 A CLOCK

              * The following command sets the USE property for  pin  scan_clk
                to CLOCK:

                Original DEF:

                - scan_clk + NET scan_clk + DIRECTION INPUT + USE SIGNAL ;

                Run setPtnPinUse to change USE to CLOCK:

                setPtnPinUSE [dbGet top.name] scan_clk CLOCK

                DEF after change:

                - scan_clk + NET scan_clk + DIRECTION INPUT + USE CLOCK ;

Related Information
              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

